We recommended and management agreed to instruct the: 

Municipal Accountant to:

transfer the financial assistance from various NGAs from the General Fund to the Trust Fund books in accordance with existing accounting policy; 

trace the records/documents relative to the unaccounted balances, reconcile the same, and remit the correct balance to the source agencies; 

consider requesting for write-off after reconciliation to resolve the dormant/long outstanding accounts and clean the account Due to NGAs for fair presentation in the Financial Statements; 

(iv) coordinate with the Municipal Treasurer for the return of unused funds to the source agencies (SAs) or to the National Treasury, as the case may be; and 

(v) draw Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) under the General Fund to recognize/adjust the amount of assets procured under the appropriate Assets accounts by taking up the following adjusting entries: 


