We recommended and management agreed to undertake the following measures:

require the LDRRM Officer to monitor the implementation of projects out of the LDRRMF to maximize the utilization of the Fund and avoid absorption of PPAs which are more appropriately chargeable against the General Fund; 






initiate the creation of three positions for DRRM staff and the eventual hiring of such mandatory positions for the LDRRM Office in compliance with NDRRMC-DILG-DBM-CSC JMC No. 2014-1; 

include in its upcoming plans the gradual compliance with the minimum standards on disaster preparedness based on available resources; and




instruct the Municipal Engineer to perform appropriate corrective measures on the defects noted on the ceiling of the evacuation facility.

We recommended and management agreed to:

adhere to the required composition of the GAD GFPS Executive Committee and Technical Working Group (TWG) and exclude/replace the members who are no longer connected in the LGU;

consider using the results of CBMS, especially the sex-disaggregated data as inputs for planning, budgeting, programming and policy formulation for the setting up and maintenance of GAD database;

